WEBVTT

00:04.963 --> 00:07.382
♪ We are The Fungies ♪

00:07.465 --> 00:10.760
♪ Prehistoric fungi
in a mushroom to-o-wn ♪

00:10.844 --> 00:12.178
♪ Outside, we look different ♪

00:12.262 --> 00:13.805
♪ Inside, we're the same ♪
Yeah!

00:13.888 --> 00:16.266
♪ Everyone's a Fungie
in their own way ♪

00:16.349 --> 00:18.643
♪ Come join The Fungies ♪

00:18.727 --> 00:21.938
♪ Explore a brand-new world
made just for yo-o-u ♪

00:22.021 --> 00:23.690
♪ If you're inclusive,
inquisitive ♪

00:23.773 --> 00:25.233
♪ Respectful, and kind ♪

00:25.316 --> 00:28.778
♪ You can be a Fungie, too ♪

00:28.862 --> 00:35.285
♪♪

00:35.368 --> 00:37.036
Hmm...

00:37.120 --> 00:38.997
Hmm.

00:39.080 --> 00:43.126
Ow.
Both of your legs
are super broke.

00:43.209 --> 00:44.753
What happened?

00:44.836 --> 00:46.296
-Uh...
-Uh, well...

00:46.379 --> 00:48.465
-Ready, Pam?
-Ready!

00:48.548 --> 00:51.509
I've never flown before,
but that shouldn't be an issue!

00:51.593 --> 00:53.178
[ Thud ]

00:53.261 --> 00:55.138
Just one of those things,
I guess.

00:55.221 --> 00:58.641
Well, luckily Mama's got
some fresh legs right here!

00:58.725 --> 00:59.976
[ Crimes ]

01:00.059 --> 01:03.146
One for Seth...

01:03.229 --> 01:04.647
Hee, thanks, Mom.

01:04.731 --> 01:07.817
Next, we'll just pop Pam's
leg off and --

01:07.901 --> 01:09.235
[ Roars ]

01:09.319 --> 01:13.072
Oh, right, yeah, guess
you gotta wear this cast.

01:13.156 --> 01:15.158
There.

01:15.241 --> 01:16.910
Now rest for a week

01:16.993 --> 01:20.663
'cause that's how long it takes
the dino bones to heal.

01:20.747 --> 01:22.207
What is rest?

01:22.290 --> 01:24.334
Is that where you got
to the bathroom?

01:24.417 --> 01:26.503
No, that's the restroom.

01:26.586 --> 01:30.715
Rest means you sit still until
your body gets better.

01:30.799 --> 01:32.175
No, thank you.

01:32.258 --> 01:33.927
Aw, don't do that.

01:34.010 --> 01:36.679
Pam, wait!
That's -- come back here!

01:36.763 --> 01:40.767
I'm fine, Seth!
I still got one good leg.

01:40.850 --> 01:43.228
Aah!
Pam!

01:43.311 --> 01:45.563
Hey! Careful.

01:45.647 --> 01:49.484
[ Grunting ] Oh, geez.

01:49.567 --> 01:52.195
All right, young lady,
until both of your legs heal

01:52.278 --> 01:53.988
you're going to be
living here

01:54.072 --> 01:55.615
in our attic!

01:55.698 --> 01:59.744
We got crosswords, puzzles,
oh, and the main attraction...

01:59.828 --> 02:01.496
the view!

02:03.748 --> 02:05.959
You can see the apartments
across the street!

02:06.042 --> 02:08.336
I pretend they're
my little dolls.

02:08.419 --> 02:09.546
Okay...

02:09.629 --> 02:11.339
So today is the first,

02:11.422 --> 02:13.925
and you just need to rest
until the seventh.

02:14.008 --> 02:16.344
If you can do that,
you'll be all better!

02:16.427 --> 02:18.555
I'm gonna go catch you
some bugs to eat.

02:18.638 --> 02:22.475
And remember, rest...

02:23.726 --> 02:26.062
Rest.

02:26.145 --> 02:29.399
♪♪

02:29.482 --> 02:32.944
Pam, I got a nice,
big, juicy -- whoa!

02:33.027 --> 02:35.238
Pam! You look terrible!

02:35.321 --> 02:38.366
I'm so bored. I can't take it.

02:38.449 --> 02:40.201
Well, w-what about
the puzzles?

02:40.285 --> 02:42.787
I did them all!

02:42.871 --> 02:44.873
Well, did you try looking out
the window?

02:44.956 --> 02:47.250
I mean, it's action
packed out there!

02:47.333 --> 02:48.668
See?

02:48.751 --> 02:50.795
Teacher Terry is lowering Gorbo
to do his business.

02:50.879 --> 02:52.422
That's fun!

02:52.505 --> 02:56.926
The clown is working on his act,
that could be entertaining!

02:57.010 --> 02:58.678
Oh! Derns and Mortins are...

02:58.761 --> 03:02.098
oh, I guess they're just having
a good time, you know?

03:02.181 --> 03:04.684
And, oh! Sharon is helping
Pooger renovate!

03:04.767 --> 03:06.853
Looks nice!
-Eh?

03:06.936 --> 03:09.230
Hardcore salmon!

03:09.314 --> 03:11.190
Uh, baby blue?

03:11.274 --> 03:14.777
Quality entertainment!

03:14.861 --> 03:18.364
Hey, no, bad Pam!
It's just that my days

03:18.448 --> 03:22.410
are usually a constant
struggle for survival.

03:22.493 --> 03:26.789
But sitting still is worse!

03:26.873 --> 03:28.499
Well, if Pam hates resting,

03:28.583 --> 03:32.086
maybe she just needs
a little drama.

03:32.170 --> 03:33.922
[ Phone rings ]

03:34.005 --> 03:35.715
Y'ello.
Sharon Carpenter.

03:35.798 --> 03:38.676
Have I got a job for you.

03:42.138 --> 03:43.264
Can't...

03:43.348 --> 03:46.476
take it...anymore!

03:46.559 --> 03:48.978
I gotta get outta here!

03:53.024 --> 03:56.152
Aah! Oh, no!

03:56.235 --> 03:58.404
What have I done?

03:58.488 --> 04:01.658
Hmm...

04:01.741 --> 04:04.035
[ Rooster crows ]

04:04.118 --> 04:06.329
Morning Pam,
how are you feeling?

04:06.412 --> 04:08.414
Rested, I --
-Shh!

04:08.498 --> 04:10.959
Last night I heard
Pooger scream.

04:11.042 --> 04:13.127
So I stayed up all night
and Sharon

04:13.211 --> 04:15.338
has been acting
really weird.

04:15.421 --> 04:18.091
[ Chainsaw whirring ]

04:18.174 --> 04:21.219
[ Gasps ] Call the cops!

04:21.302 --> 04:24.806
Now Pam, maybe Sharon was
using the chainsaw

04:24.889 --> 04:26.891
to cut up
a giant vegetable.

04:26.975 --> 04:28.267
Then where's Pooger?

04:28.351 --> 04:30.353
That is suspicious,
but we need proof.

04:30.436 --> 04:31.854
How 'bout this?

04:31.938 --> 04:34.941
I'll keep watch and you
take a nap. Sound good?

04:35.024 --> 04:36.693
I can't sleep with all this --

04:36.776 --> 04:38.695
[ Snoring ]

04:38.778 --> 04:42.198
Heh, too easy. [ Chuckles ]

04:42.281 --> 04:48.079
Rest, Pam. [ Chuckling ]

04:50.957 --> 04:52.417
Hey, buddy! How'd it go?

04:52.500 --> 04:53.710
Pam is hooked!

04:53.793 --> 04:55.753
There's no way
she'll leave the attic.

04:55.837 --> 04:57.422
Good job!

04:57.505 --> 04:59.674
I couldn't have done it without
this giant vegetable I found.

04:59.757 --> 05:01.384
Talk about a lotta sauce.

05:01.467 --> 05:05.013
And now we just gotta keep up
the ruse until Pam's legs heal!

05:05.096 --> 05:08.558
Hey, Pooger, you're okay hiding
a few more days, right?

05:08.641 --> 05:11.394
Yeah! Well...okay.

05:11.477 --> 05:13.229
Excellent, excellent.

05:13.312 --> 05:16.399
And as promised.

05:16.482 --> 05:20.153
Whether it's renovating
an apartment or faking a crime,

05:20.236 --> 05:22.488
a job's a job.

05:22.572 --> 05:23.823
What did I miss?

05:23.906 --> 05:27.243
Oh, nothing yet, but I'm sure
you'll catch Sharon.

05:27.326 --> 05:28.661
I am not leaving this window

05:28.745 --> 05:30.580
until I get
to the bottom of this!

05:30.663 --> 05:32.540
Yes, splendid, Pam.

05:32.623 --> 05:34.542
You watch that window.

05:34.625 --> 05:35.960
[ Chuckles ]

05:36.044 --> 05:40.214
♪ Oh, sittin' around
is what I do! ♪

05:40.298 --> 05:44.260
♪ Staring' out the window
and watching you ♪

05:44.343 --> 05:48.056
♪ I don't know if it will
take too long ♪

05:48.139 --> 05:52.226
♪ 'Cause I wanna see
if you do anything wrong ♪

05:52.310 --> 05:54.103
♪ Whoa-oa! ♪

05:54.187 --> 05:56.105
♪ Yeah-yeah! Yeah! ♪

05:56.189 --> 05:59.984
♪ We're gonna see! ♪

06:00.068 --> 06:01.944
♪ Whoa-oa! ♪

06:02.028 --> 06:03.696
♪ Yeah-yeah! Yeah! ♪

06:03.780 --> 06:06.115
♪ Doing something wrong! ♪
♪ Whoa-oa! Yeah-yeah! ♪

06:06.199 --> 06:07.867
♪ Yeah!
I don't sing -- Whoa-oa! ♪

06:07.950 --> 06:11.454
♪ Yeah-yeah!
♪ Oh, sittin' around
is what I do! ♪

06:11.537 --> 06:15.458
♪ Starin' out the window
and watching you ♪

06:15.541 --> 06:19.128
♪ I don't know if it will
take too long ♪

06:19.212 --> 06:23.591
♪ 'Cause I wanna see
if you do anything wrong ♪

06:23.674 --> 06:25.051
Hey Pam, look!

06:25.134 --> 06:27.762
You're almost all --
And I'm done.

06:27.845 --> 06:30.014
-What?
-I got all the evidence!

06:30.098 --> 06:31.849
Sharon is crazy guilty.

06:31.933 --> 06:33.559
Let's call the authorities
so they can

06:33.643 --> 06:35.228
throw her in the slammer.

06:35.311 --> 06:37.313
Uh, yeah, but, you think
maybe you need

06:37.396 --> 06:38.898
some more evidence, though?

06:38.981 --> 06:40.817
I've gotten everything
I'm gonna get.

06:40.900 --> 06:43.194
Frankly, Sharon's starting
to repeat herself.

06:43.277 --> 06:47.031
[ Chainsaw whirring ]

06:47.115 --> 06:49.492
There's just nothing left
for me to do now.

06:52.078 --> 06:54.122
Ugh, one more day.

06:54.205 --> 06:56.040
Oh! But Pam, wait!

06:56.124 --> 06:57.959
You haven't found
Sharon's accomplice!

06:58.042 --> 06:59.418
Accomplice?

06:59.502 --> 07:02.171
Every criminal worth their salt
has a partner.

07:02.255 --> 07:04.173
Criminals love group projects.

07:04.257 --> 07:07.093
And if you turn in Sharon
without finding her partner,

07:07.176 --> 07:09.345
her partner's gonna
come and get you.

07:09.428 --> 07:11.681
Get you good!
[ Gulps ]

07:11.764 --> 07:13.850
So you just stay there
and keep watching that window

07:13.933 --> 07:15.852
and find Sharon's accomplice.

07:17.895 --> 07:20.189
Who else could it be?

07:20.273 --> 07:21.983
[ Gasps ]

07:22.066 --> 07:23.734
[ Planter shatters ]
Gorbo!

07:26.195 --> 07:29.866
What am I missing?

07:29.949 --> 07:34.203
Hmm, who's your partner,
Sharon?

07:34.287 --> 07:35.913
[ Gasps ] Seth!

07:35.997 --> 07:38.708
Yes, it's all so simple.

07:38.791 --> 07:40.835
Pooger must have discovered
some science.

07:40.918 --> 07:42.295
Ah!

07:42.378 --> 07:44.463
Seth wanted that science
real bad,

07:44.547 --> 07:46.257
but Pooger was standing
in his way,

07:46.340 --> 07:49.468
so Seth hired Sharon
to take care of Pooger.

07:49.552 --> 07:52.555
Hello?

07:52.638 --> 07:55.933
And now he's gonna
get rid of me, too!

07:56.017 --> 07:59.312
Oh, Pam! I'm home!

07:59.395 --> 08:03.566
I'm walking towards the attic!

08:03.649 --> 08:05.943
Now I'm in the attic!

08:06.027 --> 08:07.778
Oh, no, this is it.

08:07.862 --> 08:10.448
Pam, you've been
such a good detective

08:10.531 --> 08:14.160
that I brought you
a bowl of bugs for dinner!

08:14.243 --> 08:15.828
Mmm...

08:15.912 --> 08:17.705
Pam: I bet those bugs
are poisoned!

08:17.788 --> 08:20.583
[ Screeches ]
Ah!

08:20.666 --> 08:22.710
Oopsies.

08:22.793 --> 08:24.212
Oh, that's okay!

08:24.295 --> 08:27.882
But don't worry, I have
another surprise for you!

08:28.382 --> 08:29.592
[ Gasps ]

08:29.675 --> 08:31.302
I...

08:31.385 --> 08:33.930
ordered some
more index cards

08:34.013 --> 08:37.225
for your conspiracy board.

08:37.308 --> 08:40.102
Whew.
Yeah, how's that
going by the way?

08:40.186 --> 08:41.854
Oh, bad. I gave up.

08:41.938 --> 08:45.233
Well, maybe I can help you out.
Still have Sharon on there.

08:45.316 --> 08:47.902
That's good.
Ruled out the clown?

08:47.985 --> 08:49.946
I don't know about that.

08:50.029 --> 08:52.448
Hey, hold on, mastermind?

08:52.531 --> 08:54.617
Uh, Pam?

08:54.700 --> 08:56.452
Aah! Oof!

08:56.535 --> 08:58.579
YOU made Pooger go away.

08:58.663 --> 09:00.998
Okay, technically that's true,
but --

09:01.082 --> 09:03.459
And now you wanna
take me out, too!

09:03.543 --> 09:07.713
W-what? Wait a sec.
It's the seventh!

09:07.797 --> 09:10.883
Pam, your legs should be
healed by now!

09:10.967 --> 09:13.094
Good.

09:13.177 --> 09:16.764
Now it's a fair fight.

09:16.847 --> 09:18.307
[ Roars ]
-Aah!

09:18.391 --> 09:20.101
Come back, you bad kid!

09:20.184 --> 09:25.064
Ah! This is bad! Whoa!
[ Roars ]

09:25.147 --> 09:26.524
I don't like it!

09:26.607 --> 09:28.526
[ Panting ]

09:28.609 --> 09:31.362
Please!
I was only trying to help!

09:31.445 --> 09:35.533
Yeah, help me kick the bucket!

09:35.616 --> 09:37.326
Gorbo, Gorbo!

09:40.037 --> 09:41.998
Just --
just let me explain!

09:42.081 --> 09:44.208
Never!

09:44.292 --> 09:46.502
Aah!

09:46.586 --> 09:49.213
Wow, Mortins,
you're getting really good.

09:49.297 --> 09:52.174
I need this for a second.
Hey, we're playing!

09:55.928 --> 09:58.681
Give it back!

09:58.764 --> 10:00.141
-Ha!
-Yum.

10:00.224 --> 10:04.395
Aah!

10:04.478 --> 10:07.023
[ Growls ]
Whoa!

10:07.106 --> 10:09.358
[ Cups shatter ]
[ Growls ]

10:09.442 --> 10:12.695
What an act.
Aah!

10:12.778 --> 10:14.405
-[ Growling ]
-Ah, ah!

10:14.488 --> 10:17.658
I always knew it would end
like this between us.

10:17.742 --> 10:21.412
-Really?
-[ Growls ]

10:21.495 --> 10:24.540
Huh?

10:24.623 --> 10:26.208
Hi, Pam.

10:26.292 --> 10:28.711
Pooger, you're...alive!

10:28.794 --> 10:31.547
That's what I was
trying to tell you!

10:31.630 --> 10:33.215
I know it's hard for you
to sit still,

10:33.299 --> 10:36.135
so I made
an exciting distraction.

10:36.218 --> 10:38.804
Pooger and Sharon
were just acting.

10:38.888 --> 10:40.222
Seth paid me money
to do acting

10:40.306 --> 10:43.017
and I was very good at it.

10:43.100 --> 10:46.354
Well, it did help.
My legs feel as good as new!

10:46.437 --> 10:49.482
Thanks, Seth.
-We're here for the party!

10:49.857 --> 10:52.568
[ Horn honking ]

10:52.651 --> 10:58.115
♪♪

10:58.199 --> 11:00.409
Hey, Seth, next time
I break a bone,

11:00.493 --> 11:03.079
do you think you can fake
a bank heist for me to stop?

11:03.162 --> 11:05.414
For you, Pam?
Make it two banks.

11:05.498 --> 11:11.045
♪♪

11:17.968 --> 11:20.304
What am I missing?
